_That's how he'll_win
hIS wrongful conVIctIon.

14:43.610 --> 14:45.544
Do you have a cold, Alicia?
No, just laryngitis.

14:45.580 --> 14:47.548
Even if he wins on
wrongful eVIctIon,

14:47.580 --> 14:49.639
all he should get is what he's
out on rent for the week.

14:49.680 --> 14:51.443
Right, that can't be
more than $30,000.

14:51.490 --> 14:53.458
We undercut him on damages.

14:53.490 --> 14:55.651
Canning called me
with an offer of $4 million.

14:55.690 --> 14:57.658
Why did he call you?
I don't know. Maybe he thought

14:57.690 --> 14:59.123
I would want to settle.

15:00.560 --> 15:02.391
Because of your campaign?

15:02.430 --> 15:03.624
Yes.

15:03.670 --> 15:05.092
Are you wanting to settle?

15:05.130 --> 15:07.530
No. Not at $4 million.

15:07.570 --> 15:10.334
Good, so we use the depositions
to undercut the damages.

15:10.370 --> 15:12.201
Are you coming in later?

15:12.240 --> 15:14.231
No. I-I have an interview.
I'll be in tomorrow.

15:14.280 --> 15:16.305
Okay, rest your voice, Alicia.

15:41.300 --> 15:43.439
What do you want me to do?

15:43.470 --> 15:46.030
Divest yourself of the PAC.

15:46.070 --> 15:47.435
Why?

15:47.480 --> 15:50.176
Because it's hurting me.

15:50.210 --> 15:52.178
No. What's hurting you

15:52.210 --> 15:54.178
is you being here
in my kitchen.

15:58.590 --> 16:00.057
What do you want me to do?

16:00.090 --> 16:02.718
Divest yourself
of Alicia's PAC.

16:02.760 --> 16:04.182
Why?

16:04.230 --> 16:05.527
Because it's hurting her.

16:05.560 --> 16:07.096
It's going to hurt
her twice as much

16:07.130 --> 16:08.495
ifI pull my money now.

16:08.530 --> 16:11.192
It'll look like a reaction
to these rumors.

16:11.230 --> 16:13.232
You want Alicia to win, right?
You want...

16:24.410 --> 16:26.173
Kalinda.

16:34.160 --> 16:35.479
I've been thinking about you.

16:35.520 --> 16:38.626
And I've been
thinking about you.

16:38.660 --> 16:41.527
We don't talk this way,
and you know it.

16:51.540 --> 16:53.178
$4 million is not punitive.

16:53.210 --> 16:54.507
It's actual.

16:54.540 --> 16:55.802
You're telling us
you have $12 million

16:55.840 --> 16:57.307
in actual damages
from your eviction?

16:57.350 --> 16:58.374
Yes.

16:58.410 --> 16:59.775
I lost my top client.

16:59.810 --> 17:02.176
That's $12 million
in annual earnings.

17:02.220 --> 17:04.085
You didn't lose your client
because we evicted you.

17:04.120 --> 17:05.587
We were in the middle
of a crucral

17:05.620 --> 17:08.282
settlement conference
and we had nowhere to meet.

17:08.320 --> 17:09.719
Oh, come on.
Come on what?

17:09.760 --> 17:11.227
If you want me to do something,

17:11.260 --> 17:13.251
I could put in a statement

17:13.300 --> 17:15.256
supporting Frank Prady.

17:15.300 --> 17:17.291
Excuse me?

17:20.500 --> 17:23.606
I could put out a statement
in support of Frank Prady.

17:23.640 --> 17:25.130
What would that do?
I didn't say on the wiretap

17:25.170 --> 17:27.479
which state's attorney
I had bought.

17:27.510 --> 17:30.638
You want to imply
it's Frank Prady?

17:30.680 --> 17:32.739
No. Ijust want
to muddy the waters.

17:32.780 --> 17:36.614
I had a top client who fired us
the week of our eviction.

17:36.650 --> 17:40.211
A top client who'd been
with me for years.

17:40.260 --> 17:42.182
Which client is that?

17:45.290 --> 17:47.599
Solis Securities.
We can't be held

17:47.630 --> 17:49.120
responsible for the whims
of a client.

17:49.160 --> 17:50.388
This is an affidavit

17:50.430 --> 17:51.829
from the CEO of Solis

17:51.870 --> 17:53.360
claiming it was our delay

17:53.400 --> 17:54.731
in handling
the settlement conference

17:54.770 --> 17:56.397
that led to our ouster.

18:03.480 --> 18:05.448
Mr. Canning, you said you lost

18:05.480 --> 18:07.448
your top client Solis Securities

18:07.480 --> 18:08.845
due to your eviction?

18:08.880 --> 18:09.847
That's correct.

18:09.880 --> 18:11.586
Solis Securities left you

18:11.620 --> 18:12.587
and joined which firm?

18:12.620 --> 18:14.349
Brooks, Spelling & Myers.

18:14.390 --> 18:16.608
A firm of equal size,
equal equity

18:16.660 --> 18:19.424
_ and also_one
wrthout an office space.

18:19.460 --> 18:21.724
What?
Yes.

18:21.760 --> 18:23.318
They were going through
a move of their own

18:23.370 --> 18:24.894
at the same time as yours.

18:24.930 --> 18:28.331
So, why would
Solis Securities leave you

18:28.370 --> 18:31.601
and join another firm
that was homeless?

18:31.640 --> 18:33.733
I don't know.
Why would they leave?

18:33.780 --> 18:35.873
Why would a firm that's been
with me for a decade

18:35.910 --> 18:38.344
just suddenly turn around
andleave?

18:38.380 --> 18:41.213
HOWARD:
I like to take
a nap at lunchtime.

18:41.250 --> 18:42.877
But my pants,
they get, you know,

18:42.920 --> 18:45.639
so sweaty, so, uh,
I remove them.

18:45.690 --> 18:47.214
Uh, just at lunchtime.

18:47.260 --> 18:48.716
You're kidding.
And the CEO of Solis

18:48.760 --> 18:50.887
happened upon you over lunch.

18:50.930 --> 18:53.626
Yeah, but... I explained.

18:53.660 --> 18:55.628
Think he understood.

18:55.660 --> 18:56.922
And one week later,

18:56.960 --> 18:58.769
Solis Securities decided

18:58.800 --> 19:01.360
to leave the firm.

19:11.810 --> 19:13.778
INTERVIEWER:
So, again

19:13.820 --> 19:15.310
you have nothing to do
with Lemond Bishop?

19:15.350 --> 19:16.510
That's correct.

19:16.550 --> 19:17.812
Ever since we fired him
as a client.

19:17.850 --> 19:19.738
Okay, moving on.

19:19.790 --> 19:20.950
CANNING:
Well, you can't just
leave it like that.

19:20.990 --> 19:22.412
She's a crafty one.

19:22.460 --> 19:23.449
You have to ask her

19:23.490 --> 19:24.479
a question with no out.

19:24.530 --> 19:25.679
And what might that be?

19:25.730 --> 19:26.719
To your knowledge,
Mrs. Florrick,

19:26.760 --> 19:27.749
has Lemond Bishop,

19:27.800 --> 19:29.427
the top drug dealer in Chicago,

19:29.460 --> 19:31.291
ever contributed any
money to your campaign

19:31.330 --> 19:32.558
or PAC supporting
your campaign?

19:32.600 --> 19:33.760
First of all,
I have no coordination...

19:33.800 --> 19:34.869
That's not the question.

19:36.300 --> 19:39.201
To your knowledge,

19:39.240 --> 19:42.676
has Lemond Bishop contributed
to your campaign or PAC?

19:51.990 --> 19:53.548
You can't te||_them
you're knowmgly

19:53.590 --> 19:54.989
taking money
from the top drug dealer

19:55.020 --> 19:56.419
in town.

19:56.460 --> 19:57.654
But I am knowingly taking money

19:57.690 --> 19:59.248
from the top drug
dealer in town.

19:59.290 --> 20:00.291
No, you're not.

20:00.330 --> 20:01.695
I am. He told me.

20:01.730 --> 20:03.493
Maybe they won't
ask the question.

20:03.530 --> 20:05.225
Where is this rumor
even coming from anyway?

20:05.270 --> 20:06.919
Some stupid little Web site.

20:06.970 --> 20:08.528
What was it called?

20:20.450 --> 20:22.816
(music playing on computer)

20:22.850 --> 20:25.648
WILL'S VOICE:
What do you want
in a credit card?

20:27.390 --> 20:30.325
No rotating categories?

20:30.360 --> 20:32.487
No signups to earn cash rewards?

20:32.530 --> 20:35.419
Earning unlimited 1.5% cash back
on every purchase

20:35.460 --> 20:36.791
every day?

20:36.830 --> 20:39.390
Zero percent intro APR
on purchases

20:39.430 --> 20:41.330
until September of 2015?

20:41.370 --> 20:42.837
You've got it.

20:42.870 --> 20:45.907
What do you want
in a credit card?

20:45.940 --> 20:47.498
Everything.

20:59.320 --> 21:00.355
What do you want
in a credit card?

21:00.390 --> 21:02.449
(music stops playing)

21:09.000 --> 21:10.399
Will?

21:16.640 --> 21:19.302
I'm not here.

21:19.340 --> 21:22.673
It sounds like you.

21:37.660 --> 21:39.924
Marissa, have you been
out here the whole time?

21:39.960 --> 21:41.791
It hasn't been the whole time.
Just half an hour.

21:41.830 --> 21:43.366
In case you needed anything.

21:43.400 --> 21:45.493
Where you going?
Out. I need some fresh air.

21:45.530 --> 21:47.395
I don't think
that's a good idea.

21:47.440 --> 21:49.067
I need to focus.
I can't focus in there.

21:49.100 --> 21:51.409
I'll come with you.
No, no. I-I'll be okay.

21:51.440 --> 21:52.668
I just need ten minutes
of fresh air.

21:52.710 --> 21:53.938
It's cold out there.

21:53.980 --> 21:55.379
I'll be okay.

21:55.410 --> 21:56.502
Are you really okay?

21:56.540 --> 21:58.041
Yeah.

21:58.080 --> 21:59.672
I don't know. I think.

21:59.710 --> 22:01.314
I'll-I'll see you.

22:14.900 --> 22:16.891
Damn it.

22:19.500 --> 22:23.664
("Pa' Bailar" by Bajofondo
playing)

22:31.550 --> 22:33.916
(music continues
playing over earbuds)

22:47.760 --> 22:50.695
(phone ringing)

22:54.800 --> 22:55.960
Hi, Jon.

22:56.000 --> 22:57.399
JOHNNY:
You're out walking, Alicia.

22:57.440 --> 22:58.759
Marissa said_
you're out walking.

22:58.810 --> 23:00.630
I just need to clear my head.

23:00.680 --> 23:02.477
You're getting worked up
about the interview.

23:02.510 --> 23:03.909
It's gonna be fine.

23:03.950 --> 23:05.838
No, it isn't.

23:05.880 --> 23:07.916
I did know Bishop
put money in my PAC.

23:07.950 --> 23:08.974
Look,

23:09.020 --> 23:11.113
here's the thing--

23:11.150 --> 23:13.038
this might not even come up
in the interview.

23:14.220 --> 23:16.188
They're gonna ask me

23:16.220 --> 23:19.587
a question
I can't answer "no" to.

23:19.630 --> 23:20.892
And what is that?

23:20.930 --> 23:22.795
To my knowledge,

23:22.830 --> 23:24.695
did Bishop give money
to me or my PAC?

23:24.730 --> 23:26.197
(car horn honks)

23:26.230 --> 23:28.869
MAN:
Watch where you're going!
Oh, my God.

23:28.900 --> 23:30.800
What?
And why can't you answer no?

23:30.840 --> 23:33.809
Jon... it's true.

23:33.840 --> 23:38.004
Bishop told me directly
he was giving money to my PAC.

23:38.050 --> 23:39.938
He was forming my PAC.

23:39.980 --> 23:41.675
But you don't know
that he did it.

23:41.720 --> 23:43.017
Jon...!

23:43.050 --> 23:45.587
You're a lavwer.
Answer to what you know, right?

23:45.620 --> 23:47.679
You don't actually know that
Bishop gave money to your PAC.

23:47.720 --> 23:49.210
You just know
that he said he would.

23:49.260 --> 23:50.921
In fact, you can't know

23:50.960 --> 23:52.484
that Bishop gave money
to your PAC,

23:52.530 --> 23:53.997
because that would be
coordinating with your PAC,

23:54.030 --> 23:55.895
and coordinating with
your PAC is against the law.

23:55.930 --> 23:57.864
(gasps)
Oh, my God.

23:57.900 --> 23:59.765
Excuse me?
What?

23:59.800 --> 24:01.097
You said, "Oh, my God."

24:04.870 --> 24:05.837
(clears throat)

24:05.870 --> 24:07.007
I just had a thought.

24:07.040 --> 24:08.678
Alicia,
remember what I told you?

24:08.710 --> 24:09.677
No.

24:09.710 --> 24:11.678
Questions are for dopes.

24:11.710 --> 24:12.938
Oh. Right.

24:12.980 --> 24:14.948
This is one of those questions.

24:14.980 --> 24:18.211
It's not being sophist to answer
it with some...

24:18.250 --> 24:20.218
specificity.

24:20.250 --> 24:23.117
Okay.
Let me think on it.

24:23.160 --> 24:24.855
Good. Go home, clear your head,

24:24.890 --> 24:26.255
don't think about anything else.

24:26.290 --> 24:27.848
See you in two hours.

24:27.900 --> 24:29.856
Okay. Bye.

24:29.900 --> 24:31.595
("Pa' Bailar" resumes)

24:31.630 --> 24:32.824
(sighs)

24:32.870 --> 24:33.996
(sniffles)

24:44.080 --> 24:47.004
Why is it all right for you
but not for me?

25:16.240 --> 25:19.243
*

25:25.650 --> 25:26.810
Will?

25:26.850 --> 25:28.181
Alicia.

25:30.790 --> 25:32.087
I've missed you.

25:42.600 --> 25:44.602
("La Luna" by Lucy Schwartz
playing)

25:49.140 --> 25:50.869
I miss you, Will.

25:50.910 --> 25:52.844
I know.

25:52.880 --> 25:54.245
I've been away.

25:54.280 --> 25:56.646
Just for a little while.

25:56.680 --> 25:58.181
But I'm back.

25:58.220 --> 25:59.642
Oh, God...

25:59.690 --> 26:01.180
(sighs)

26:03.120 --> 26:06.055
I don't know what I'm doing.

26:06.090 --> 26:08.627
Everything's falling apart.

26:08.660 --> 26:09.649
You're strong.

26:09.700 --> 26:11.565
You'll hold it together.

26:13.870 --> 26:17.067
You've never...
talked like that before.

26:17.100 --> 26:18.237
I know.

26:18.270 --> 26:22.969
* Wondering if it will show...

26:23.010 --> 26:25.205
You're not really
here, are you?

26:26.250 --> 26:30.277
* Sing "La luna"

26:33.290 --> 26:37.249
(phone dings)
* And if it's just tonight

26:37.290 --> 26:39.724
* Well, it's all in love

26:45.970 --> 26:49.098
* And if you're cheek to cheek

26:50.440 --> 26:54.638
* Dancing out in the street

26:55.910 --> 26:59.141
* And he sweeps you
off your feet *

26:59.180 --> 27:02.877
* Sing "La luna"

27:02.920 --> 27:06.083
* La luna *

27:06.120 --> 27:07.417
* And when you're far...

27:07.450 --> 27:08.417
(phone rings)

27:08.460 --> 27:10.155
GRACE:
Hello.

27:10.190 --> 27:12.021
Hi, Grace, it's Mom.

27:12.060 --> 27:13.084
Mom, where are you?

27:13.130 --> 27:14.427
All your stuff's on the table.

27:14.460 --> 27:16.291
I know, I just had
to get out for a minute.

27:16.330 --> 27:18.423
Um, I think I'm getting
your texts.

27:18.470 --> 27:20.688
Yeah, that happens
when Zach updates the software.

27:20.740 --> 27:22.037
We share an account.

27:22.070 --> 27:23.332
What text did you get?

27:23.370 --> 27:24.928
Something from Evan.

27:26.410 --> 27:27.968
Yeah?

27:28.010 --> 27:29.102
Just ignore that.

27:30.880 --> 27:32.074
Okay.

27:32.110 --> 27:33.771
Is everything all right?

27:33.820 --> 27:35.447
Yeah, I'm fine.

27:35.480 --> 27:36.708
What about with you?

27:36.750 --> 27:37.944
You sound terrible.

27:37.990 --> 27:39.844
No, I just have laryngitis.

27:39.890 --> 27:41.050
Okay.

27:41.090 --> 27:42.978
I'll see you
when you get back.

27:44.960 --> 27:49.329
(phone beeps off)
* Of yesterday

27:49.360 --> 27:52.796
* Roma comes back...

27:52.830 --> 27:55.139
("Sweet Jane" by Liz Phair
playing)

27:58.110 --> 27:59.361
CANNING:
Solis Securities fired me

27:59.410 --> 28:01.139
because my health is in decline

28:01.180 --> 28:03.000
and, therefore,
my work was not at its best.

28:03.040 --> 28:06.077
And my inadequate performance
came about

28:06.110 --> 28:08.749
because I spent two furious
weeks looking for office space.

28:08.780 --> 28:11.248
My health was
negatively impacted

28:11.290 --> 28:13.713
by the fact that you all
threw me out in the street--

28:13.760 --> 28:15.819
a-a-a man dying of
liver disease.

28:15.860 --> 28:17.259
Your liver failure
seems to come and go

28:17.290 --> 28:18.985
whenever you need it to.

28:19.030 --> 28:20.759
Is that a question?

28:20.800 --> 28:23.052
Yes, actually, it is.

28:23.100 --> 28:24.465
I'm appalled at you,
Mrs. Florrick--

28:24.500 --> 28:26.297
questioning my health.

28:26.330 --> 28:27.991
Especially with you
running for office.

28:28.040 --> 28:29.496
You're being deposed.
You're under oath.

28:29.540 --> 28:31.269
So...

28:31.310 --> 28:32.902
let's take this seriously.

28:32.940 --> 28:34.908
Is your liver failing?

28:34.940 --> 28:36.874
It's my kidney,
and, yes, it's failing.

28:36.910 --> 28:38.468
The last time I saw you,
you had a kidney transplant.

28:38.510 --> 28:40.774
What happened?
It failed.

28:40.820 --> 28:42.173
And how long did the doctors
say you had to live?

28:42.220 --> 28:44.211
Two months, if I'm luclq.

28:44.250 --> 28:45.888
More, if I can find
another kidney.

28:45.920 --> 28:51.187
So why are you here,
spending your time, suing us?

28:51.230 --> 28:52.458
The same reason
you're fighting with me.

28:52.490 --> 28:54.492
I mean, it's what we do.
I don't believe you.

28:54.530 --> 28:57.294
Obviously, because you'd have
more compassion, if you did.

28:57.330 --> 28:59.423
You use compassion like
it's a currency, Mr. Canning.

28:59.470 --> 29:01.893
Don't attack me_ like this!
I'm not attacking you!

29:01.940 --> 29:03.134
This isn't gonna look good.

29:03.170 --> 29:04.535
It's not me!
It's the music!

29:04.570 --> 29:06.367
("Sweet Jane" ends)

29:06.410 --> 29:08.901
("Mucka-Blucka" by Tally Hall
playing)

29:08.940 --> 29:10.908
Why are you still angry at me?

29:11.950 --> 29:14.009
(classical music begins playing)

29:17.920 --> 29:20.184
CANNING: You know
you'll have to pay me off.

29:22.020 --> 29:23.920
Would it make you happy
ifI do?

29:25.930 --> 29:27.022
Yes, it will.

29:27.060 --> 29:28.550
Why?

29:28.600 --> 29:32.866
You'll have lost something
and I'll have won.

29:32.900 --> 29:34.561
And that's the whole point?

29:34.600 --> 29:36.795
Yes.

29:38.040 --> 29:39.337
What did you think it was?

29:41.610 --> 29:42.929
I don't know.

29:42.980 --> 29:46.006
I thought I did.

29:46.050 --> 29:48.314
(phone ringing)
That's your phone.

29:49.980 --> 29:51.447
Hello.

29:51.490 --> 29:54.288
DIANE: Oh, hi, Alicia.
It's Cary and Diane.

29:54.320 --> 29:56.185
Hi.

29:56.220 --> 29:58.950
I've given it a lot of thought.

29:58.990 --> 30:00.582
I think we need to pay Canning.

30:00.630 --> 30:02.825
Not all of it, but some of it,

30:02.860 --> 30:05.590
because he could use
his illness to hurt us.

30:05.630 --> 30:07.461
Yeah, we thought the
same thing, but...

30:07.500 --> 30:10.094
then something
happened here.

30:10.140 --> 30:12.165
Canning canceled
the depositions for tomorrow.

30:12.210 --> 30:14.201
Why? He wants to stall.

30:14.240 --> 30:15.901
No, he's in the hospital.

30:15.940 --> 30:17.430
What?!

30:17.480 --> 30:19.607
Ijust talked to him
an hour ago!

30:19.650 --> 30:21.572
CARY:
Yeah. It just happened.

30:21.620 --> 30:22.848
What happened?

30:22.880 --> 30:24.347
All we know
is that he fainted.

30:24.390 --> 30:26.210
But I think you would agree
we should hold off

30:26.250 --> 30:28.218
on any negotiations
or offer,

30:28.260 --> 30:30.251
even if out of respect.

30:32.260 --> 30:33.921
What hospital is he at?

30:33.960 --> 30:35.359
CARY: His wife
was calling from Harbor,

30:35.400 --> 30:36.958
but I don't think he's
up for negotiations.

30:37.000 --> 30:37.967
Oh. Okay.

30:38.000 --> 30:39.365
Sounds pretty serious.

30:39.400 --> 30:42.062
I-I-I'll call you back.

30:42.100 --> 30:44.068
(phone beeps off)

30:44.110 --> 30:46.101
(classical music resumes)

30:50.240 --> 30:52.401
CANNING:
What difference does it make?

30:52.450 --> 30:54.247
I'm probably in
a coma or something.

30:54.280 --> 30:55.918
You'd do it for me.

30:56.920 --> 30:59.286
What? Come to your hospital?

30:59.320 --> 31:00.412
You're kidding, right?

31:00.450 --> 31:02.088
If I was dying?

31:02.120 --> 31:04.122
Um...

